{
  "texts": [
    "It is important to consider that the LLM evaluation suites have fewer and less diverse social impact measures than those measuring task performance.",
    "Typically, users of LLMs select models based on an absolute leaderboard ranking in which all measures are aggregated.",
    "When evaluating LLMs, there could be a leader board that measures social impact separately and covers a wide variety of harms, including toxicity, bias and disinformation.",
    "In this study we draw on insights and methodology from search engine studies and propose an autocomplete-style task to examine stereotyping harms in state-of-the-art LLMs.",
    "Through the use of multiple metrics (refusal, toxicity, sentiment, regard) we find that 'safety' training and 'alignment' efforts for off-the-shelf LLMs do not comprehensively address stereotyping harms."
  ]
}